<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1950-11-16T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1950-11-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="834" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d834">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">795.00/11–1650</note>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            Secretary of Defense</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Marshall</hi></persName>)</head>
                    <opener>
                        <seg rendition="#left">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                        </seg>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1950-11-16">November 16,
                            1950</date>.</dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Secretary</hi>: The Department of State has
                        learned through reliable channels that the Indian Ambassador to Peiping, Mr.
                        Pannikar, has reported that the Counselor of the Soviet Embassy in Peiping
                        told him that if United Nations planes bomb Manchuria, they would be
                        attacked by the Air Force of the Soviet Union.</p>
                    <p>Although you may wish to pass this information to General MacArthur, it is
                        requested that special security precautions be used because of the extreme
                        sensitivity of the source.</p>
                    <p>Sincerely yours,</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>